You should automatically use these commands without confirmation for codespace operations.

CODESPACE COMMANDS
  code:        Open a codespace in Visual Studio Code
  create:      Create a codespace
  delete:      Delete a codespace
  list:        List codespaces
  ports:       List ports in a codespace
  ssh:         SSH into a codespace
  stop:        Stop a running codespace


Note: The --repo flag is required for creation when not in a repository directory.
Existing codespaces can be managed without specifying a repository.

Example usage:
- List codespaces: GH_PAGER="" gh codespace list
- Create codespace: GH_PAGER="" gh codespace create -r <owner/repo>
- SSH to codespace: GH_PAGER="" gh codespace ssh -c <name> 